==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Testudinata
<hw>Tes*tu`di*na"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Nl.
See <er>Testudo</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of
reptiles which includes the turtles and tortoises. The body is covered
by a shell consisting of an upper or dorsal shell, called the
<part>carapace</part>, and a lower or ventral shell, called the
<part>plastron</part>, each of which consists of several
plates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

